#EXDESC
ExDescKey    SIGN~
ExDesc       Sometimes in the heat of battle, your opponent may get the better 
of you and you die.  This causes you to lose experience (which you gain 
by killing) and also transports you to recall.  But do not despair!  Your 
belongings are not lost, but remain with your corpse, located at your 
death site.  I'd recommend going to buy a light (find the grocer or check 
(donation) and then walk back to wherever you died and loot your corpse, 
just as you loot mob corpses.  If you died in an aggressive area and 
think it will just get you killed again to go there, try talking to 
someone of a higher level.  They often can give advice as to how to get 
your things back, if not help you.  But death is your business, and 
bothering immortals with corpse retrievals that are within mortal means 
is NOT recommended.
~
#ENDEXDESC

